Citic Pacific, China Eastern Airlines, Sinopec: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-04-04T00:15:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/citic-pacific-china-eastern-airlines-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  rose 1.2 percent to 23,801.90. The Hang
Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, rose 1 percent to 13,451.48.  Citic Pacific Ltd. (267)  (267 HK): The Hong Kong steelmaker and
property developer said an internal investigation committee
found no evidence of fraud in relation to the legal advice it
received before disclosing a failed derivatives bet in 2008. The
stock gained 3.7 percent to HK$22.40.  China Eastern Airlines Corp. (670 HK): The nation’s second-
largest carrier was cut to “hold” from “buy” by Du Jianping,
an analyst at Bank of China Ltd. The stock declined 0.3 percent
to HK$2.98.  China Petroleum & Chemical Corp. (386)  (386 HK): The company’s
Chairman Su Shulin took over as deputy party secretary in  Fujian
province , the Fujian Daily reported, citing a government
official. Sinopec, as the company is known, increased 0.3
percent to HK$7.82.        Man Sang International Ltd. (938)  (938 HK): The pearl distributor
said Chief Executive Officer Thomas Lee Kang Bor, 57, resigned
to spend more time on his own business. He was re-designated as
a non-executive director. The stock fell 4.1 percent to 47 Hong
Kong cents.  Minmetals Resources Ltd. (1208)  (1208 HK): The Hong Kong unit of
China’s biggest metals trader made an unsolicited offer of about
C$6.3 billion ($6.5 billion) in cash for Equinox
Minerals Ltd. Minmetals increased 4 percent to HK$6.56.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in  Tokyo  at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 